text:
I continued experimenting after it started to click. I’m doing a bunch of data munging at work and so had a go at basic table manipulation, while also trying out the function format:
```
[
db: [
    [Name: "Ted", Age: 37, Weight: 176],
    [Name: "Nguyen", Age: 50, Weight: 160],
    [Name: "Sita", Age: 28, Weight: 143]
  ],
  keys: [a=&gt; a?.[v=&gt; k=&gt; :: [k?]]],
  keys test: #data.keys?,
  del: [a=&gt; {l: a?.1, k: a?.2,
    l?.[v=&gt;&gt; (v? ! k?, v?)]}
  ],
  del test: [[a, r, w], r].del?,
  pick: [a=&gt; {l: a?.1, kl: a?.2,
    kl?.[v=&gt;&gt; :: [v?: l?.v?]]}
  ],
  pick test: [#data, [A, C]].pick?,
  delkey: [a=&gt; {l:a?.1, d:a?.2, 
    [l?, [l?.keys?, d?].del?].pick?}
  ],
  delkey test: [#data, B].delkey?,
  delcol: [a=&gt; {t: a?.1, c: a?.2, 
    t?.[v=&gt;&gt;[v?,c?].delkey?]}
  ],
  delcol test: [db?, Weight].delcol?,
]
```

